{
  "stem": "21786.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "When she arrived on the spot, I tried always to find something for her to shield her, the same way in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But I don't think that she would need it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "She was pretty on her own.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The fact that she came so late, after the war, was that she was-- she escaped from a death march, and was found by the Russians, who took her to the commanding officer, who took some liking in her.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And she became a cook for the division.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then he became enchanted with her and didn't want to let her go.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So she literally had to escape from the Russians where she was-- they were, at that point, somewhere around the outskirts of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have to correct you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On my father's side, it was-- father had to make some kind of an exception when he married my mother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For father's family was, actually, far more religiously involved than we were.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My uncle, Heinrich-- H-E-I-N-R-I-C-H-- was a very practicing Jew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my relatives who lived-- my two aunts who lived in Germany, they were practicing Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My uncle Heinrich didn't have any children, so I was somehow the favorite son at that point.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "On my mother's side, it was quite a different story.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This little place where my grandfather was-- was-- lived and was born, and my mother was born, they were the only Jews in the village.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in the vicinity of the village, there were other little towns and villages.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There might have been, I don't know, two dozen Jewish-- two dozen Jewish families living in a radius of about 25 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they had this little shul, and they had this little cemetery.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Already, my grandfather wasn't practicing too much.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
